The paper discusses the development of a musculoskeletal robot with a brain-like neural controller, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of a neuromorphic computing platform (SpiNNaker) and closed-loop cerebellar model for neural control suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The scalability aspect of the system also implies a potential interest in systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of Myorobotics as a framework for musculoskeletal robot development suggests a possible focus on machine learning (cs.LG) for optimizing the system.
